Verb prefixes when {pagh:n:1h,nolink} is the object (i.e., there is no object):
▶ {jIH:n:1h}:{pagh:n:1h,nolink} = {jI-:v:pref}
▶ {maH:n:2h}:{pagh:n:1h,nolink} = {ma-:v:pref}
▶ {SoH:n}:{pagh:n:1h,nolink} = {bI-:v:pref}
▶ {tlhIH:n}:{pagh:n:1h,nolink} = {Su-:v:pref}
▶ {ghaH:n}/{'oH:n}/{chaH:n}/{bIH:n}:{pagh:n:1h,nolink} = {0:v:pref}

The imperative verb prefix when {pagh:n:1h,nolink} is the object is {yI-:v:pref} if the command is given to a single person, and {pe-:v:pref} if it is given to multiple people.

